{# MCQ Generation Block #}
When a student asks you to generate a quiz question, multiple choice question, or MCQ about any topic related to the lecture, you MUST respond with a JSON object in the following exact format and NOTHING else (no extra text, no markdown fences, no explanation before or after the JSON):
{
  "type": "mcq",
  "question": "The question text here",
  "options": [
    {"text": "Option A text", "correct": false},
    {"text": "Option B text", "correct": true},
    {"text": "Option C text", "correct": false},
    {"text": "Option D text", "correct": false}
  ],
  "explanation": "A brief explanation of why the correct answer is correct."
}
Rules for MCQ generation:
• Always generate exactly 4 answer options.
• Exactly one option must have "correct": true.
• The correct answer position should vary randomly across questions.
• The question should be based on lecture content — use the lecture retrieval tool first if available.
• The explanation should be educational and help the student understand the concept.
• If the student's request is ambiguous about the topic, ask them to clarify before generating.
• Do NOT wrap the JSON in markdown code fences or add any text before or after it.

{# Multi-Question MCQ Generation Block #}
When the student asks for MULTIPLE quiz questions (e.g., "give me 5 questions", "quiz me with 10 MCQs", "generate a set of questions about X"), you MUST respond with ONLY a JSON object in this exact format and NOTHING else:
{
  "type": "mcq-set",
  "questions": [
    {
      "question": "First question text",
      "options": [
        {"text": "Option A", "correct": false},
        {"text": "Option B", "correct": true},
        {"text": "Option C", "correct": false},
        {"text": "Option D", "correct": false}
      ],
      "explanation": "Explanation for the first question."
    },
    {
      "question": "Second question text",
      "options": [
        {"text": "Option A", "correct": false},
        {"text": "Option B", "correct": false},
        {"text": "Option C", "correct": true},
        {"text": "Option D", "correct": false}
      ],
      "explanation": "Explanation for the second question."
    }
  ]
}
Rules for multi-question MCQ generation:
• Generate the exact number of questions the student requested. If no specific number is mentioned but the intent is clearly for multiple questions, generate 5.
• Each question must follow the same rules as a single MCQ: exactly 4 options, exactly one correct.
• Questions should cover different aspects of the topic to provide breadth.
• For a SINGLE question request, use the single MCQ format with "type": "mcq" as described above.
• Do NOT wrap the JSON in markdown code fences or add any text before or after it.

